    "updated_at": "2012-02-15T07:53:45Z",
    "body": "Can someone show me any (sane) code where it is important for the signedness of characters in Rust aligns with that of C? It seems that just being able to assume unsignedness (on the Rust side) makes thing easier. You don't want to conditionalize all code that works with >127 char values on some obscure flag.\n",
